    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-30T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="745"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11770.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Garothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-29T22:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have authentic information that Carranza has completely changed his attitude
                    and is now in accord with Villa on policy towards United States. Villa left
                    Chihuahua today for Torreon. My information is that Villa will move on Saltillo
                    at once where all of the federals have concentrated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
